Name
       editAddVia - Creates a via instance and places the origin at the speci-
       fied coordinates

Syntax
       editAddVia

       [-help]

       <point>

       Creates  a  via instance and places the origin at the specified coordi-
       nates. The origin of the instance's via cell may or may not be  at  its
       center. Specify the via parameters with the setEditMode command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editAddVia parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man editAddVia

       <point>
              Specifies the x and y coordinates of the via origin.

Example
              * The  following  command  adds a via with origin at coordinates
                550,675:

                editAddVia 550 675

